Master Machine :
Ansible installtion :

Steps :
1 Install Ansible on master
2 Configure SSH access to Ansible Host
3 Setting up Ansible Host and testing Connection


=> 1 Install Ansible on master(Control Server)


Commands:

Sudo apt-get update
sudo apt install software-propeties-common  (Latest Verions and updates)
sudo apt-add-repository ppa:ansible/ansible   (To add ansible in third party Repository and Press Enter)
sudo apt update (Update the machine)
sudo apt install Ansible
Sudo ansible --version

=> 2  Install in Slave Machine - Slave Server

Below commnds needs to be run in slave (Hosts machine).
Host Machine Commands :

sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install python

=> 2 Configure SSH access from control amchine to slave server (Host machine)

How connect from Control Master Server to Slave server (Host machine) ?
- ssh ubuntu@<Ip address of the slave>

To check ssh file
- cd .ssh
(Optional )- cat authorized_keys

To generate ssh key 
- ssh-keygen 
Commnads :
cd .ssh
ls

